Raw dev notes -- Shipping Cost Calculator: React + TypeScript Desktop App (Feb 2026)

Built a shipping cost calculator for a logistics client. React + TypeScript frontend,
packaged as a desktop app. Pulls zone data and pricing from spreadsheet files.

Key work this month:
- Broke down a monolithic component into 6 focused ones
- Fixed all 52 TypeScript errors for a clean production build
- Added comprehensive test suite (74 tests with vitest)
- Built localStorage persistence for form state
- Custom app icon for the desktop build
- Improved tip clarity: combined related surcharges, added specific thresholds
- Pallet warning redesign
- Made surcharge reduction suggestions actionable

Struggles:
- ESLint v9 breaking changes hit during the refactor
- Data parser needed caching to avoid redundant fetches
- npm output capture is flaky in GitBash -- had to redirect to temp files

The calculator now handles multi-item shipments with proper dimensional weight,
pallet surcharges, and generates PDF quotes. The test suite covers 74 scenarios
across different weight ranges and destinations.
